Paramedics at the scene say they found a police van lying on its roof after being hit by a light vehicle. JOHANNESBURG Three police officials have been injured in an accident in Midrand at Old Pretoria Road.Paramedics say they found a police van lying on its roof after being hit by a light vehicle.ER24's Russel Meiring says, We discovered that three officers had sustained only minor injuries. Fortunately no serious or fatal injuries were reported on the scene, and paramedics treated the patients had to transport them to a hospital in Midrand for further treatment. 